(74, 1, '2017-12-28 14:48:11', '2017-12-28 14:48:11', '              <div class=\"col-md-12 text-center\">\r\n                  <h2 class=\"siteDescription font24 text-left\"><span>FALL WALK-IN TOURS EVERY SATURDAY IN OCTOBER </span> NO RESERVATION REQUIRED\r\n                  </h2>\r\n              </div>\r\n              <div class=\"col-md-12\">\r\n                  <p> Maryâs Land Farm is a 160 acre working farm located in Howard County three miles from the intersection of Route 108 and Route 32. The farm is based on a permaculture method of farming which is healthy for the environment, employees and visitors. Most importantly, we produce healthy, organic produce and meat products.</p>\r\n                  <p>\r\n                  On the farm we raise layer chickens, layer ducks, meat chickens (broilers), goats, Katahdin sheep, Red Devon beef, ponies, and rare and shy unicorns.</p>\r\n                  <p>\r\n                  We have installed three miles of swales and berms to keep rainwater on the property and to avoid runoff into our stream, which flows in the Patuxent.</p>\r\n                  <p>\r\n                  We offer field trips to schools, daycare programs, after school programs, scout groups, homeschoolers, and families up and down the East Coast.</p>\r\n                  <p>\r\n                  Our educational programs are catered to the requirements of the age group visiting the farm. Our passion is programs that educate children on the intersection of farming and the environment in a fun, informal hands-on atmosphere that supplements the classroom curriculum. We look forward to aiding whatâs taught in the classroom and can build a custom field trip to compliment your curriculum. With each field trip, we provide material that can be used in the classroom before or after the trip.</p>\r\n              </div>', 'FIELD TRIPS', '', 'inherit', 'closed', 'closed', '', '17-revision-v1', '', '', '2017-12-28 14:48:11', '2017-12-28 14:48:11', '', 17, 'http://webdev.wordpress-developer.us/mary-land-farm/17-revision-v1/', 0, 'revision', '', 0),
(75, 1, '2017-12-28 14:54:22', '2017-12-28 14:54:22', '<h2 class=\"siteDescription\"><span>UNICORN PARTIES</span></h2>\r\n                  <img src=\"images/unciright.jpg\" alt=\"\" class=\"alignright\">\r\n                 <p>All parties are onsite at our farm on a patio or under a large pavilion and in a heated party room when it is cold outside! Riding the unicorn is still done outside. Parties include a unicorn and a mini horse for petting and decorating as well as a well dressed and well spoken handler.  Up to 16 child guests are welcome. We provide (1) eight foot banquet table for food and refreshments. We provide a low table with seating for 15 children and the guest of honor.  The guest of honor must be turning 5 or under to have a Unicorn or Princess Party.  There is a 65lb weight limit to ride on the pony. The standard party is a maximum of two hours in duration, including one hour with the pony, miniature horse, and handler. We provide the carrots for the carrot feeding at the end of the party.  We also provide the decorations for the mini Horse, pony and Unicorn.</p>\r\n\r\n                  <p>Parties are rain or shine as the pony rides can be done inside an open arena.  However, if the weather is severe, we will discuss rescheduling or cancellation with you by phone.</p>\r\n                  \r\n                  <p>We do not provide party decorations, food, a face painter nor a balloon twister, but you are more than welcome to bring them with you as long as they contact us one week in advance at <a href=\"tel:4108494314\" class=\"red\"><b>410-849-4314</b></a>.</p>\r\n                  <p>Reservations Are Made Online at Party Reservation.</p>\r\n                  <p>Additional tables must be rented from us by filling out the <a href=\"#\" class=\"red\"><b>Adult table reservation</b></a>.</p>\r\n                  \r\n                  <div class=\"yellowBg\">\r\n                    <p>Unicorn with a rainbow mane is $50 extra due to the labor involved in painting the mane.</p>\r\n                    <p>If the time or day slots below are not showing as available, please call Maria at <a href=\"tel:2392277152\"><b>(239) 227-7152</b></a>. We are having issues with the reservation system.</p>\r\n                  </div>', 'PONIES & UNICORNS', '', 'inherit', 'closed', 'closed', '', '19-revision-v1', '', '', '2017-12-28 14:54:22', '2017-12-28 14:54:22', '', 19, 'http://webdev.wordpress-developer.us/mary-land-farm/19-revision-v1/', 0, 'revision', '', 0),
